// Experiment Registry: metadata for all interactive experiments.
// Each entry defines id, name, category, lazy-load module path, and
// key talking points.
//
// To add a new experiment:
//   1. Implement a class extending BaseExperiment in
//      `./<category>/<id>.js`. Override at minimum `init()`,
//      `activate()`, `deactivate()`, `update(dt)`, `buildControls(el)`
//      and (optionally) `getInfoPanel()`.
//   2. Append an entry to EXPERIMENTS below with `id`, `name`,
//      `category` (one of EXPERIMENT_CATEGORIES below), a
//      `module: () => import('./<category>/<id>.js?v=<cache-key>')`
//      lazy-loader, and a short `description` + `keyPoints` blurb.
//   3. To create a brand-new category, push to EXPERIMENT_CATEGORIES.
//
// Bump the `?v=...` cache key in the module URL whenever you ship
// a code change so the browser fetches the new module.

